# Working method

- Inspect existing tree, naming, and tests before editing; Sparky is early—prefer small, coherent additions over large reshuffles.
- Make the smallest complete change that satisfies the task and PLAN.md.
- Do not rename top-level Ansible/compose layout without an explicit PLAN-driven reason.
- When adding features, cite the PLAN section you are implementing (in commit message or PR body).

## Completion checklist

- No committed secrets or real `.env` files.
- New or changed routes reflected in OpenAPI/registry files when those files exist.
- Tests or smoke scripts updated when behavior is user-visible.
- Documentation touch (`docs/` or PLAN cross-links) when operator steps change.
